<div id="review_1718633704" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1718633704" />
    <a title="Kirsten " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/833700-kirsten"><img alt="Kirsten " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607003371p2/833700.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1718633704?book_show_action=true">Aug 04, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kirsten " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kirsten " href="/user/show/833700-kirsten">Kirsten </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/13649086-the-yard">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/833700-kirsten?shelf=nearly-made-me-cry">nearly-made-me-cry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1718633704" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13600470625615094210">I absolutely LOVED this book! <br/><br/>This book is an incredible ensemble piece. It is well structured and has engaging characters. But no one character shows up as the central character, instead it is a story about a homicide unit. One of the very first. <br/><br/>A lot of attention to life in Victorian London is put into the book. You see the horrible disparate life between the 1% and the great unwashed horde. But the author instead of just putting the facts out there, he includes them in a very emotional way. </span>
  <span id="freeText13600470625615094210" style="display:none">I absolutely LOVED this book! <br /><br />This book is an incredible ensemble piece. It is well structured and has engaging characters. But no one character shows up as the central character, instead it is a story about a homicide unit. One of the very first. <br /><br />A lot of attention to life in Victorian London is put into the book. You see the horrible disparate life between the 1% and the great unwashed horde. But the author instead of just putting the facts out there, he includes them in a very emotional way. It was so effective that I nearly cried at one point. <br /><br />I will definitely move on with this book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13600470625615094210" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
